    <text id="A2908T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>In this letter to her brother, Margaret discusses Enos's desire for a military
                    transfer and the family's daily events.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient">Arbor Hill V<hi rend="super">a</hi>
                        <lb/>Nov 14<hi rend="super">th</hi><lb/>Mr Enos Ott<lb/>Camp
                        Lee<lb/>Richmond</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1864-11-13">Nov 13<hi rend="super">th</hi> 1864</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Brother</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I received your letter friday come thursday I am at Aunt Sallies at this time
                    come yesterday <orig reg="evening">evning</orig> Eliza Estaline Elec are here
                    Elec and I are going to M<hi rend="super">r</hi> Shueys this <orig reg="evening"
                        >evning</orig> going home tomorrow Miss Lizzie Strain and I come to M<hi
                        rend="super">r</hi> Shueys <orig reg="Wednesday">wedsday</orig>
                    <orig reg="evening">evning</orig>. Eliza Es and Elec come to M<hi rend="super"
                    >r</hi> Shuey friday <orig reg="evening">evning</orig> yesterday we went to
                    Staunton. Elec got your letter down and one from Henry both were written the 6
                    both come thursday I was glad to <orig reg="hear">here</orig> from you both. I
                    am sorry <abbr expan="cannot">cant</abbr> get home. what ever you do <abbr
                        expan="do not">dont</abbr> you ask for a transfer for <orig reg="cavalry"
                        >caverlery</orig> for if you get a transfer to the <orig reg="valley"
                    >vally</orig> in <orig reg="infantry">infentry</orig> you <abbr expan="cannot"
                        >cant</abbr> stand the march and will get home that is all the hope I have
                    for you to get home and that is Henrys hope <pb n="2"/>we got a letter from
                    Henry a few days before Henry wrote to you he <orig reg="hadn't">hadent</orig>
                    <orig reg="heard">hird</orig> from you <orig reg="since">cense</orig> he left
                        <orig reg="there">thare</orig>
                    <orig reg="said">sayed</orig> he was <orig reg="disappointed">disapointed</orig>
                    you <orig reg="didn't">dident</orig> get off but <orig reg="hoped">hopt</orig>
                    you <orig reg="might">mite</orig> get a <orig reg="transfer">transfur</orig> to
                    the valley if you <orig reg="couldn't">couldent</orig> get off I think your best
                        <orig reg="chance">chans</orig> is to get a <orig reg="transfer"
                    >transfur</orig> to infantry if you go to <orig reg="cavalry">cavelery</orig>
                    you are in for the war, if you live you will see that. Henry and Frank Mc. <orig
                        reg="have">hase</orig> been <orig reg="transferred">transfurd</orig> to the
                    4 <abbr expan="Company">comp</abbr>
                    <orig reg="Liberty">Libberty</orig> Hall Va. the same <abbr expan="Company"
                    >Co</abbr> Baxter was in it was Franks doings they <orig reg="didn't"
                    >dident</orig> want to <orig reg="separate">sepperrate</orig> you try for the
                    same if you can get in I would much rather they both had stayed in the Middle
                    Brook Co but as it is you three had better be together when we send to one send
                    to both if <orig reg="any">aney</orig> thing happens one we <orig reg="can">cane</orig>
                    <orig reg="hear">here</orig>
                    <orig reg="from">frome</orig> one or the other as we are so close. <orig
                        reg="Do">doo</orig> the best you can and trust in the Lord he can take care
                    of each one of us we are <orig reg="getting">geting</orig> a long very well
                        <orig reg="considering">considehering</orig> you both a way if your <orig
                        reg="health">helth</orig> and lives are spared we can <orig reg="sort of"
                        >sorto</orig> make out a while. Jinnie and Bec went home yesterday Eliza met
                    them friday they <orig reg="were">wer</orig> going to <orig reg="their"
                    >ther</orig> Uncles friday night. Jinnie <orig reg="has">hase</orig>
                    <orig reg="her">hir</orig>
                    <orig reg="veil">vail</orig> I think <pb n="1"/><del rend="none" hand="h1"/> the one <del
                        hand="h1"/> hundred <orig reg="couldn't">couldent</orig> take that one but
                    told Elec to go to new Port and report what one to let them have but I told Elec
                    to <unclear>write</unclear> H geff and to get off if he I must close w<add
                        hand="h1" place="inline">r</add>ite soon they all send <orig reg="their"
                        >there</orig> love to you</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Ever your Sister</salute>
                    <signed>Mag H Ott</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
